              "number": 7,
              "content": "&nbsp;These words are taken from Browning’s poem “Rabbi Ben Ezra” (1281/1864). The lines emphasize optimistically that the most fulfilling part of one’s life should be its final years, those which are “yet to come.” For one’s earlier years—in a life well spent—should be preparation for the well-being, wisdom, and peace that come with experience and old age.",
