              "content": "&nbsp;The noted English Mathematician and Philosopher&nbsp;Alfred North Whitehead (d. 1367/1974) stated: “Philosophy is the product of wonder,” which echoes the words of Socrates (d.&nbsp;): “Wonder is the beginning of wisdom”&nbsp;Greek:&nbsp;<em>Di</em><em>á</em><em>&nbsp;t</em><em>ò thaumázein hē sophía,</em><em>&nbsp;Διά τὸ θαυμάζειν ἡ σοφία</em>), which is cited in the images below. In Greek,&nbsp;<em>sophía</em><em>,&nbsp;</em><em>σοφία</em><em>&nbsp;(wisdom) and Philosophy—“the love of wisdom” from&nbsp;</em><em>ph</em><em>í</em><em>los</em>,&nbsp;<em>φίλος</em>&nbsp;(love) and&nbsp;<em>sophía</em><em>,</em><em>σοφία</em><em>&nbsp;(wisdom)—dovetail nicely.&nbsp;</em>",
