          "title": "Earlier Academic Publications",
          "level": 5,
          "content": "<ul><li>“The Nature of Ethical Speculation in ash-Shāṭibī’s Thought,” in&nbsp;<em>The Maghreb Review</em>, VI (1981), pp. 19-26.</li><li>“Fasting” and “Friday Prayers,” in&nbsp;<em>The Encyclopedia of the Middle Ages</em>, 1981.</li><li>“The Perceptible and the Unseen: The&nbsp;Qur’ānic&nbsp;Conception of Man’s Relationship to God and Realities beyond Human Perception,” in&nbsp;<em>Mormons and Muslims: Spiritual Foundations and Modern Manifestations</em>&nbsp;(Provo, UT: Bringham Young University, Religious Studies Center: 1983), pp. 153-204.</li><li>“Abû&nbsp;Ḥanîfah,” in&nbsp;<em>Encyclopaedia Iranica</em>, (London etc.: Routledge &amp; Kegan Paul, 1983), 1:295-301.</li><li>“The&nbsp;Qur’ānic&nbsp;Conception of the Word,”&nbsp;<em>A University of Michigan Memorial Edition on the Word in Honor of the Late Professor James Bailey</em>, ed. Roy Rappaport, 1984.</li></ul>",
